     896                 :            : 
     897                 :            :           // The basis functions chosen for the DG method are the Dubiner
     898                 :            :           // basis, which are Legendre polynomials modified for tetrahedra,
     899                 :            :           // which are defined only on the reference/master tetrahedron.
     900                 :            :           // Thus, to determine the high-order solution from the left and right
     901                 :            :           // elements at the surface quadrature points, the basis functions
     902                 :            :           // from the left and right elements are needed. For this, a
     903                 :            :           // transformation to the reference coordinates is necessary, since
     904                 :            :           // the basis functions are defined on the reference tetrahedron only.
     905                 :            :           // Ref: [1] https://doi.org/10.1007/BF01060030
     906                 :            :           //      [2] https://doi.org/10.1093/imamat/hxh111

     910                 :            :           // basis functions on the left element.
